main event: An unidentified bright starlike object was sighted over the Pacific Ocean on December 13, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as starlike with a bright appearance., It appeared to rise from the horizon to the object with an aurora-like light., The object had an observed course of 240 degrees T and rose from 360 degrees T., Reports were unclassified and delivered to DIA and NTN., The ship's position during the sighting was 33N 143E.
location: Pacific Ocean, Unknown Region, Unknown Country
witness description: No witnesses were explicitly mentioned in the report.
